Title: Dirac's Legacy

Comments: Talk presented at the International Conference on Orbis Scientiae

1996 Miami Beach Florida- January 25-28, 1996In recent years light-cone quantization of quantum field theory has emergedas a promising method for solving problems in the strong coupling regime. Thisapproach has a number of unique features that make it particularly appealing,most notably, the ground state of the free theory is also a ground state of thefull theory.